1.  OS ka main purpose kya hota hai?
    OS ek middleman hai — user aur hardware ke beech. Iska kaam hai programs ko efficiently run karne do aur 
    resources (CPU, memory, disk) manage karo.
    Interview Tip: Yaad rakho: OS = Manager. Hardware = Factory. User = Customer.

2.  Kernel kya hota hai?
    Kernel OS ka core hota hai — ek bridge jo applications aur hardware ke beech kaam karta hai. 
    Ye CPU time, memory, aur device drivers manage karta hai. System calls ke through applications kernel se baat karte hain.
    Interview Tip: Analogy: OS = hotel, Kernel = hotel manager jo har department control karta hai.

3.  OS aur Kernel mein kya difference hai?
    OS complete software package hai (kernel + shell + GUI + utilities) . Kernel sirf OS ka core part hai. 
    OS user aur hardware ke beech interface provide karta hai; Kernel specifically hardware aur applications ke beech bridge hai.
    Interview Tip: Yaad rakho: Kernel ⊂ OS. Kernel always runs in privileged mode.

4.  Monolithic kernel kya hota hai?
    Monolithic kernel mein sab kuch — CPU scheduling, memory management, file system, drivers — ek hi address space mein hota hai.
    Iska faida ye hai ki sab fast hota hai (no inter-process communication needed), lekin koi bhi bug poore OS ko crash kar sakta hai.
    Linux iska example hai.
    Interview Tip: vs Microkernel: Monolithic = sab ek ghar mein, Microkernel = alag alag compartments.

5.  Multiprogramming kya hota hai?
    Multiple programs ko ek saath main memory mein rakhna taaki CPU hamesha kuch na kuch execute kare. Agar ek program I/O wait 
    mein hai toh CPU doosre ko execute kare. Goal = CPU utilization maximize karna.
    Interview Tip: vs Multitasking: Multiprogramming = multiple programs memory mein. Multitasking = rapid switching (user interaction ke saath).

6.  Time-sharing system kya hota hai?
    Multiprogramming ka logical extension jahan CPU itni tezi se switch karta hai ki lagta hai multiple users simultaneously use kar
    rahe hain. Har user ko lagta hai CPU sirf unka hai. Modern OS sab time-sharing use karte hain.
    Interview Tip: Analogy: ATM queue — sab ko lagta hai ATM unka hai, actually ek ek karke serve hota hai.

7.  Multitasking kya hota hai?
    Multiple tasks concurrently run ho rahi hain ek hi system mein, CPU share karke. OS ki feature hai.
    Multithreading ek single process ki feature hai; Multitasking OS level pe hoti hai.
    The CPU rapidly switches between tasks, giving each a small time slice, so they appear to run simultaneously.
    Interview Tip: Difference: Multithreading = ek process ke andar. Multitasking = multiple processes OS level pe.

8.  Interrupts kya hote hain?
    Hardware ya software signal jo CPU ko batata hai ki koi urgent kaam hai. CPU current process rok ke Interrupt Service Routine (ISR)
    execute karta hai phir wapas aata hai. Hardware interrupt (keyboard, disk) aur Software interrupt (trap, exception).
    Interview Tip: Trap vs Interrupt: Interrupt = hardware signal. Trap = software interrupt (usually error ya system call).

9.  Trap aur Trapdoor kya hota hai?
    Trap = software interrupt, usually error condition se trigger hota hai (divide by zero, invalid memory access).
    Non-maskable aur highest priority.
    Trapdoor = secret unauthorized entry point in program, intentionally left by developer for backdoor access — security vulnerability.
    Interview Tip: Security alert: Trapdoor = backdoor = security risk.

10. Bootstrap program kya hota hai?
    Computer on hone pe jo pehla program run hota hai woh bootstrap program hai. ROM/EEPROM mein stored. POST (Power-On Self Test) karta hai, 
    hardware check karta hai, phir disk se OS bootloader load karta hai jo OS ko RAM mein load karta hai.
    Interview Tip: Sequence: Power On → Bootstrap → POST → Bootloader → OS loads.

11. Assembler ka kya function hota hai?
    Assembler assembly language code ko machine code (binary/object code) mein convert karta hai.
    Input = assembly instructions (.asm file).
    Output = object code jo computer directly samjhe.
    Compiler se alag — compiler high-level language translate karta hai.
    Interview Tip: Chain: Source code → Compiler → Assembly → Assembler → Object code → Linker → Executable.

12.  GUI kya hota hai?
    Graphical User Interface — icons, windows, buttons ke through user computer se interact karta hai (mouse/touch).
    CLI (Command Line Interface) ka alternative. OS ke upper layer pe hota hai. Windows, macOS, Android sab GUI OS hain.
    Interview Tip: GUI vs CLI: GUI = easy but slow. CLI = hard but powerful (developers prefer CLI).

13. Cycle Stealing kya hota hai?
    DMA ka ek mode — I/O controller CPU se ek memory bus cycle "churaata" hai briefly RAM access ke liye, bina CPU ko interrupt kiye.
    CPU ek cycle ke liye memory access nahi kar pata lekin completely stop nahi hota. Isse I/O aur CPU kaam saath karte hain efficiently.
    Interview Tip: vs Full DMA: Cycle stealing = CPU partially runs. Full DMA = CPU completely idle during transfer.

14. Multiprocessor system ke advantages kya hain?
    Enhanced performance (workload split across CPUs), multiple applications simultaneously, multi-tasking within application, 
    high throughput aur responsiveness, hardware sharing among CPUs (memory, I/O). Scalable systems build ho sakte hain.
    Interview Tip: Types: Symmetric (sab CPU equal) vs Asymmetric (master-slave).

15. Real-time systems kya hote hain?
    Response time guaranteed hona chahiye within specific deadline. 2 types: Hard real-time (deadline miss = system failure, jaise pacemaker,
    airbag) aur Soft real-time (deadline miss = degraded performance, jaise video streaming). Special scheduling algorithms use hote hain. 
    Interview Tip: Hard vs Soft: Hard = life or death. Soft = inconvenient but not fatal.

16. What are OS problems without an OS?
    Bina OS ke: Poor resource management (koi CPU/memory management nahi), No user interface, No file system (data organize nahi),
    No networking, No error handling. Essentially impossible for normal users to use the computer.
    Interview Tip: Summary: OS = baaki sab kuch possible banata hai. Bina OS ke = raw hardware sirf developers use kar sakte.
     



    

    

